gomodel:SYNGO_972  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The role of PPP3R1 (called CNB1 in this article) is investigated using a mouse line that specifically knocks out PPP3R1 in Purkinje cells. In this mouse line, LTP is eliminated at the parallel fiber -> Purkinje cell synapse (figure 2A). Other synaptic parameters, including LTD (Figure 2) or paired pulse plasticity (Figure 3) are not affected.\n\nThe names used for the mouse line are a confusing. PPP3R1 is a regulatory subunit of PP2B (calcineurin).. Experimental description: Mutant mice in which calcineurin was selectively deleted from Purkinje cells (L7-PP2B mutant) were obtained using the Cre-loxP-system, with loxP sites flanking the regulatory subunit (CNB1) of calcium/calmodulin-activated protein phosphatase 2B (referred to as PP2B-loxP) (Zeng et al., 2001)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_972" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

